{
  "texts": [
    "The Avg-TopK method aims to eliminate the drawbacks of both max pooling and average pooling methods.",
    "It is an approximate value that represents all pixels by selecting the top k highest entries from the input data.",
    "The average value of the k pixels with the highest values is determined.",
    "(3) represents the mathematical expression of the Avg-TopK pooling method.",
    "(2) X represents the set of elements with pixels according to the pool size value selected from the data coming from the convolution layer."
  ]
}